<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-646-889  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 646 889.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 4 1990 v4 n41 p1(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Net management in works at Apple. (AppleTalk Management Protocolfor local area networks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product development).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   AppleTalk (Local area network) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Network ManagementProduct DevelopmentProtocolLocal Area Networks.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Functions of Apple Management Protocol. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Margie WylieandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- Apple may soon answer administrators' pleas for help inmanaging Mac networks.andP;  But like the answer to most prayers, AppleTalkManagement Protocol (AMP) could be a mixed blessing.andM;Loosely patterned after SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol) -- whichhas become the de facto protocol for managing large multiprotocol networks --AMP is a proprietary network management protocol, sources said.andM;Using AMP, network managers will be able to monitor and control networkdevices, such as routers, bridges and servers, that have AMP interfaces.andP;  Theprotocol consists of two parts: agent and monitor.andM;The agent software feeds information to the monitor and helps control itsassociated network device.andP;  The monitor software acts as the control consolefor tracking information and controlling devices.andM;Apple will make the monitor and agents but is relying on third parties towrite AMP interfaces for their devices, sources said.andP;  AMP gives managersmore detailed control of their Mac environments than is possible under ageneric standard that caters to the lowest common denominator, such as SNMP.andO;But Apple may find it almost impossible to convince vendors to writeinterfaces for yet another protocol.andM;&quot;We were really hoping that Apple would build its management on top of SNMP,&quot;said one developer.andP;  &quot;AMP is just one more protocol that needs to be dealtwith in wide-area networks that are already drowning in protocols.&quot;andM;Router vendors, such as Shiva Corp. and Cayman Systems Inc., will build somefacilities for AMP-to-SNMP routing and translations into their products sothat Macs can be integrated into existing SNMP services, sources said.andM;The protocol also will be extensible to other platforms that have at leastone link with AppleTalk, according to the protocol specifications.andP;  An AMPagent must have an AppleTalk address to communicate with the network monitor,but the communications path between the agent and its device is up to thedeveloper.andM;Theoretically, network managers will be able to control an entire internetfrom an AMP monitor on a Mac but only if network device makers invest inwriting AMP interfaces for their devices.andM;Apple will deliver AMP's final specification to developers by early nextyear, sources said but it is unclear when users can expect the AMP monitor.andO;</TEXT></DOC>